          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Level Scheme of Au198 Determined by Analysis of High-",
                " Precision Capture Gamma-Ray Measurements"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SPECC",
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " In-pile facility at the Argonne CP-5",
                " research reactor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Reactor core with a thermal neutron flux ~2E+13",
                " n/(cm2.s) at 2 MW reactor power."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reactor spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 7.7-m Argonne bent-crystal spectrometer",
                " with a 30x30x4-mm quartz crystal. Bank of NaI crystals",
                " used to detect gamma-ray spectrum as a function of",
                " Bragg angle of bent-crystal spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin Au foil (4 x 1 x 0.010 inches)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Gamma-ray wavelengths determined relative to the",
                " 5461-A line from Hg198."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-consistency test about the diffraction maximum for",
                " a given line, applied in order to reject the runs of",
                " inconsistent values.",
                "In addition to capture gamma rays from Au198 the",
                " following gamma rays were observed:",
                " 1) Capture gamma rays from Au199. Because of the",
                "   rather large capture cross section of Au198",
                "   (~30000 b), about 17% of the Au198 atoms capture",
                "   a neutron and form Au199 before decaying to Hg198.",
                "   These double neutron-capture events identified by",
                "   observing the relative intensities of gamma rays",
                "   for two values of the neutron flux (1E13 and",
                "   2E13 n/cm2/s). The intensities of the Au197 capture",
                "   events changed by a factor of two while the Au198",
                "   capture events changed by a factor of four.",
                " 2) Capture gamma rays in Hg200. Hg199 formed from the",
                "   gold source in the pile, permitted observation of",
                "   neutron capture in Hg199 (cross section ~2000 b).",
                "   These events were looked for by comparing the first",
                "   observation taken shortly after the source was",
                "   placed in the pile with some of the last runs.",
                " 3) Gamma rays which follow beta decay of Au198 and",
                "   Au199.",
                " 4) K x-rays from Au and Hg.",
                " 5) Gamma rays from inelastic scattering of neutrons",
                "   by Au197.",
                " 6) Annihilation radiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Observed intensities corrected for:",
                ". self-absorption in the source,",
                ". absorption in matter between source and detector,",
                ". detector efficiency,",
                ". collimator efficiency,",
                ". reflectivity of the quartz crystal."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "E-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertainties in gamma-ray energies."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Average uncertainty in line intensities.",
                " The poorest measurements determined with an accuracy",
                "  of 0.05%; many intense lines determined with an",
                "  accuracy of 0.01%, and in the very best cases with",
                "  0.0077%."
              ]
            }
          ],
